<div class="policy-container ps-4 pe-4">

    <div class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> April 2026</p>
        <p>
            ExpressWrite respects your privacy. This policy explains how information is processed when you use ExpressWrite.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div id="information" class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h2>1. Information You Provide</h2>
        <p>When using ExpressWrite, you may submit:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Resume files or resume text</li>
            <li>Job listing links or job descriptions</li>
            <li>Optional feedback or bug reports</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Resume content is processed into plain text and securely transmitted for the sole purpose of generating a cover letter.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div id="storage" class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h2>2. Letter Storage & Access</h2>
        <p>
            Generated cover letters are temporarily stored on ExpressWrite servers.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Each letter is indexed with a randomly generated secure ID.</li>
            <li>Anyone with the link or ID can access the letter.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Letters are considered temporary and may be deleted at any time by the user or by ExpressWrite.
        </p>
        <p>
            When a letter is deleted, it is permanently removed from ExpressWrite storage. ExpressWrite does not retain a copy.
        </p>
        <p>
            Resume files themselves are not permanently stored.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div id="openai" class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h2>3. Use of OpenAI</h2>
        <p>
            Resume and job listing content is transmitted securely to an up-to-date ChatGPT model using the OpenAI API in order to generate cover letters.
        </p>
        <p>
            ExpressWrite does not use submitted content to train its own models.
        </p>
        <p>
            ExpressWrite does not control how OpenAI processes data. For more information, please review OpenAI’s Privacy Policy.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div id="retention" class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Resumes are not permanently stored.</li>
            <li>Letters are stored temporarily.</li>
            <li>Deleted letters are removed from ExpressWrite systems.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            ExpressWrite does not sell, rent, or trade user data.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div id="security" class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h2>5. Security</h2>
        <p>
            ExpressWrite uses HTTPS encryption to protect data in transit.
        </p>
        <p>
            While reasonable safeguards are used, no online service can guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div id="contact" class="policy-section border border-primary rounded-3 m-4 p-3">
        <h2>6. Contact</h2>
        <p>
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong> ClarenceSmith90@gmail.com
        </p>
    </div>

